    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-27T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-27T10:00:00-05:00" n="522"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/3906: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-27T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 27, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Referring to my telegram of November 18, 2 p.m., it is estimated that 7,000
                    men arrived in Cadiz in two ships including contingents of artillery, aviation,
                    transport and infantry completely motorized and equipped. Twenty 5-inch guns
                    apparently for long range and battery <pb facs="0675" n="576" xml:id="pg_576"/>
                    of anti-tank guns seen in Seville. Aviation section is constructing air
                    fortifications around city.</p>
                <p>Traffic in port has been at the maximum for the month past owing to visits of
                    numerous German vessels. War material is unloaded in a remote and enclosed
                    section of the port. Exportations at unprecedented levels. There is a shortage
                    of silver coin and the requirements to have all peseta bills stamped is causing
                    general apprehension.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
